div.div:
The suppression of Li dendrites is beneficial in terms of performance and cell safety. From a morphological perspective, Li dendrites eventually lead to electrical isolation of Li filaments (“dead” Li) in subsequent Li-stripping processes, directly causing loss of Li CE and Li anode pulverization during repeated cycles. Indeed, the control cell shows severe surface deterioration by nonuniformly distributed SEI residues and several Li filaments isolated from the substrate. However, the NDCE cells demonstrate facile Li stripping without Li isolation (

 Figure S4

). Therefore, Li dendrite inhibition with the NDCE approach is expected to be advantageous for improving the performance of LMBs.

